The paper focuses on developing supervised systems based on neural networks and kernel-based support vector machines for automatic fact-checking, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also makes use of contextual and discourse information, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and analyzing large amounts of data, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
